The paper discusses the analysis of citation relations among journals, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of principal component analysis and factor analysis is also relevant to topics in statistical inference (cs.ST) and machine learning (cs.LG). The specific example given in the paper is the delineation of a set of biochemistry journals, which could fall under the sub-categories of information retrieval for life sciences (cs.IR) or computational biology (q-bio.CB).
